ewes 507.50.\nNEW YORK PRODUCE.\nNEW YORK. June 3.\u2014Flour, dull and\nunsettled. Pork firm; mess 34.00. Lard,\nsteady midwest 13.20013.30. Sugar, raw,\nunsettled, 96 tcBt 4.80 asked: refined dull;\ngrain la ted 6.1006.20. Coffee, Rio No. 7,\n*'5* -t \\i\u2018-i\nBears Put Curb\nUpon New York\nMart Activities\nBy W. S. COUSINS,\nInternational News Service Financial\nEditor.\nNEW YORK, June 3.\u2014Rebuffed In\ntheir first attempt in a month or\nmore to turn the market downward,\nthe bears returned to their task to\nday, and, on the whole, their efforts\nbrought a greater measure of success\nthan in yesterday\u2019s hectic market.\nReports of increasing unemploy\nment in important industrial and\nmanufacturing sections of the coun\ntry, coupled with a decline in the mill\noperations of steel, equipment and\nsome of the motor companies, encour\naged the professionals in their cam<\npaign for lower prices, and a huge\nvolume of speculative shares was\nthrown on the market. The setback\nextended to a wide range of indus\ntrial shares like Steel and General\nElectric, which refused to bend un\nder yesterday\u2019s attack, and which had\nalready given a new \u201cdemonstration\u201d\nin the first hour today.\nDue For Reaction.\nSelling orders originated in large\nvolume in some of the commission\nhouses which had been enthusias\ntically bullish since the turn of the\nyear, and which according to all ac\ncounts have followed their purchases\nwith a generous sprinkling of stop-l<#;s\norders. Regardless of the long range\nfuture of stock prices, tne impression\nhas been gaining headway in Wall\nstreet that the market was due for a\ntechnical reaction following such a\nlong period of almost uninterrupted\nadvance.\nAs in the preceding session, stock\nofferings were quickly absorbed at\nconcessions from Thursday\u2019s close.\nSteel\u2019s decline to 124 provided new\nopportunities for acquiring the stock\nin investment quarters. No serious\nconsideration was given to rumors of\nan impending business recession be\nyond what is customary at this time\nof year. Money markets were well\nsupplied, and the call loan rate ruled\nat per cent.\nGeneral Motors carried its advance\nto a new peak price of 102 ini active\ntrading near the opening of the mar\nket. but this stock also ran into profit\ntaking and short selling after the\nnoon period.\n1 50L: Santos No. 4, 16*i@17%. Tallow,\nquidt: specials'to extras 7%@74&. liny*;\nfirmer; No. 1. 1.3001.30; No. 3, 1.0501.15;\nclover 101.20. Uressed poultry, firm;\nturkevs 25040; chickens 20@42; capons\n30046;' fowls 12029; ducks 1820; Long\nIsland ducks 23024. Idve poultry, irreg\nular; geese 104/12: ducks 12025; fowls 21\n@26; turkeys 30032; roosters 13; broil\ners 1S045. Cheese, quiet; state milk, fan\ncy to special 27028; Yonng Americas 2.7.\nButter, steady; receipts 20.096; creamery\nexira 43; special market 4314044. Kggs,!\neasy. Receipts 24.669; nearby white fancy\n29031; nearby state white 24028; fresh\nfirsts 21022; Pacific coast, first to ex\ntras 28032; western whites 24020; nearby\nbrowns'26030. -Potatoes, southern, 30\n10.00; Maine 5.7307.25; Bermuda 5.50010.\nSweet potatoes, Jersey basket, 1.7503.\nPITTSBURGH LIVESTOCK.\nPITTSBURGH, June 3.\u2014Hogs Re\nceipts, 3,000: market mostly steady; 230\nto 350 lbs., $9059.00: 200 to 250 lbs., 59.60\n@$U); 160 to 200 lbs.. $10@$10.20; 130\nto 100 lbs., 510.100$10.20; 90 to 130 lbs.,\nS10.10@$10.20: packing sows, $3@$7.75.\nCattle\u2014Receipts, 25. Calves\u2014Receipts.\n300; market steady: beef steers, $10,500\n$11.73; vealers, $12@$12.50. Sheep\u2014Re\nceipts, 500; market nominal, wethers,\nwethers, $7.75; top fat lambs, $14; bulk\ncall Iambs, $C@$lO; bulk spring lambs.\n?10@$16.50. j\nEAST BUFFALO LIVESTOCK.\nEAST BUFFALO. N. Y., June 3.\nHogs\u2014Receipts, 6.000; left over, $6.36;\nmarket steady; ISO to 350 lbs., $9@$9.75:\n200 to 250 lbs., $9.60@$10.10; 100 to 200\nlbs., $100 $10.25; 130 to 160 lbs., $100\n$10225;. 130 to 160 lbs., 5100510